<Verbatim PAsource="" >A police officer was </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >yester day cleared </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >of assaulting three people, including a female colleague, with CS gas spray.</Verbatim>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >Minshull Street crown court, Manchester, had heard PC Andrew Bateson, 28, had been called to a disturbance outside the Farnworth Veterans' Club in Bolton.</Verbatim>


<Verbatim PAsource="" >PC Deborah Davidson insisted no warning had been given about the spray but PC Bateson </Verbatim>
<Rewrite PAsource="" >claimed </Rewrite>
<Verbatim PAsource="" >he had been forced to act because PC Davidson was not doing her job properly.</Verbatim>



